    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "1. Starting mode:"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Controls the clutch when pulling away by increasing current in proportion to engine speed and rate of increase of engine speed.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Decel/accel shock when travelling at low speed (below 20 km/h) is eliminated by delaying clutch \"engagement\" until the N\u00b7CVT input shaft speed coincides (almost) with engine speed.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "2. Direct coupling mode:"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Directly couples the clutch when the vehicle reaches a preset speed.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "3. Drag mode:"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Maintains good low speed (below 7 km/h) characteristics by passing a small current through the clutch (approx. 0.2A) to create a \"drag torque\" when the accelerator pedal is released. Also prevents \"creeping\" and \"stalling\" by continuously feeding idle speed signals back to the ECU.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "4. Reverse excitation mode:"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Demagnetises the clutch powder (to remove residual magnetism and prevent non-releasing of the clutch) when:",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "a) The selector lever is in \"N\" or \"P\".\nb) Engine speed is 200rev/min or less. This also prevents the vehicle from being push-started.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "5. Zero mode:"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "De-energises the clutch while the output mode is shifting from mode 2 to mode 3 as the accelerator pedal is released in \"D\", \"Ds\" or \"R\".",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "B. Line pressure solenoid control"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Controls line pressure solenoid to determine torque transmission.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "C. Idle-up relay control"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Controls idle-up relay to maintain oil pressure during ABS operation.",
      "style": "normal"
    }
  ],
